00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Stanford University

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:16,000
We were waist deep into the Dirac land, the Dirac Sea.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Well, we didn't get to the Dirac Sea yet.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:23,000
But before we continue with the three-dimensional,

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,000
before I'll do a little review of the Dirac equation that we studied,

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
and then we'll go into the three-dimensional version,

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:36,000
three-space, one-time dimension, it's a real world Dirac equation.

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:43,000
But before we do, let's go back and review, not review,

9
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:49,000
generalize what we said about second quantization, the field theory,

10
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:54,000
the fields governing multiple particle systems.

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,000
We made them out of creation and annihilation operators.

12
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:02,000
What's the difference between fermions and bosons in that respect?

13
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:12,000
And the difference is simple, not so intuitive, but rather straightforward.

14
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:24,000
If you have two bosons, you can put them into the same state, number one.

15
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
And, no, no problem.

16
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Okay.

17
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,000
So, I'm putting them into the same state.

18
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:38,000
And what's more, the creation and annihilation operators all commute with each other.

19
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Nothing particularly odd about things which commute with each other.

20
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:51,000
There is something very odd about things which anticommute with each other.

21
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:56,000
So, let's talk about anticommutation.

22
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Supposing we have two particles, and we want to say that when we interchange them,

23
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:11,000
that the wave function or the state vector should change sign.

24
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:16,000
So, let's think about what that would mean for these operators that we're constructing.

25
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:22,000
A particle at x and another particle at y.

26
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Particle one now stands for which slot?

27
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,000
This is slot one.

28
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,000
This is slot two.

29
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,000
This stands for particle one.

30
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,000
This stands for particle two.

31
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
X stands for the position of particle one.

32
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Y stands for the position of particle two.

33
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Neither x nor y refers to the x and y coordinates.

34
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:47,000
X and y are each, if you like, three-dimensional positions or one-dimensional positions, depending on the context.

35
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:51,000
That's a state with two particles, one at x and one at y.

36
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
For both, the state vector is the same.

37
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,000
It's the same.

38
00:02:54,000 --> 00:03:06,000
For bosons, this is exactly the same thing as putting particle one at position y and particle two at position x.

39
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
They're equal to each other.

40
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:16,000
So, in particular, that would tell you, how do you make a particle at x and particle y?

41
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:22,000
You take psi of x times psi of y.

42
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,000
A creation.

43
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,000
This should be creation operators.

44
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:33,000
A creation operator for a particle at x, a particle at y, and you hammer on the vacuum.

45
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:39,000
You let them act on the vacuum, and that creates particle at x and y.

46
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Supposing I want to interchange particle x and, or the two particles.

47
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:49,000
That's just interchanging x and y.

48
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,000
That would be, sorry, dagger at y.

49
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Psi dagger at x.

50
00:03:54,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Also vacuum.

51
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Good.

52
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Now, why is this true?

53
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,000
It's true because the psi's commute with each other.

54
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:12,000
You can interchange them.

55
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:17,000
This and this are related very simply by interchanging the two operators here.

56
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,000
And if they commute, that just says that psi dagger at x is a vacuum.

57
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:26,000
That just says that psi dagger of x times psi dagger of y is the same as psi dagger of y times psi dagger of x.

58
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:32,000
And so it's guaranteed that with the objects and the theories that we've been making up till now,

59
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:38,000
that they satisfy this kind of Bose statistics, this kind of Boson rules.

60
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Now, for fermions, the rule is exactly the same, but with a minus sign.

61
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Remember that the state vector of a system is the same as the state vector of a system.

62
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Remember that the state vector of a system, the real physical observable state vector of a system,

63
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:56,000
doesn't care about the sign here.

64
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:02,000
But in keeping track of the formulas, it's important to know that for fermions,

65
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:06,000
if you interchange the two particles, you get a minus sign.

66
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:13,000
That must mean that for fermions, if psi here is representing fermions,

67
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,000
that this is the top equation here.

68
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:22,000
The top formula is minus the bottom formula.

69
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:30,000
And the mathematics that goes with this is just a statement that for fermions,

70
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
the fields anti-commute.

71
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,000
So let's write out what that means.

72
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:42,000
It means psi dagger of x times psi dagger of y equals minus this over here.

73
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:46,000
But let's shift it to the left-hand side and write that plus.

74
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Plus psi dagger of y, psi dagger of x equals zero.

75
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:03,000
This object, if you take two operators, and you take their product,

76
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:08,000
and instead of subtracting in the opposite order, you add in the opposite order,

77
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:12,000
that's called the anti-commutator.

78
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:29,000
And it's written, instead of a square bracket, instead of a square commutator,

79
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,000
usually written with a curly bracket,

80
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:40,000
psi dagger of x, psi dagger of y equals zero.

81
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:44,000
In general, when you go from fermions to both,

82
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:52,000
you just take every commutation relation and replace it by an anti-commutation relation.

83
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,000
And that's how you go from fermions to bosons.

84
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,000
Now that has, let's see, is there anything else?

85
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Yeah.

86
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:02,000
First of all, it's quite clear that you can't have two particles in the same state.

87
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:07,000
For example, supposing you wanted to put two particles at the same point.

88
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,000
You want to put two particles at the same point.

89
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,000
That corresponds to...

90
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,000
Let's get rid of this over here.

91
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:21,000
That corresponds to acting with creation operators at the same point.

92
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:26,000
But, this equation over here, or let's say this one over here,

93
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:30,000
that tells us that psi dagger of x,

94
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
psi dagger of x,

95
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:36,000
times psi of x,

96
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:39,000
psi dagger of x,

97
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,000
plus psi dagger of x,

98
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,000
times psi dagger of x,

99
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:49,000
that's the anti-commutator of psi dagger of x with itself.

100
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:52,000
I've just replaced y by x,

101
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:56,000
and the statement here is that that should be equal to zero.

102
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Well, this operator and this operator are exactly the same.

103
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:05,000
This is just twice psi dagger of x times psi dagger of x equals zero.

104
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:08,000
And if something is equal to...

105
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,000
If twice something is equal to zero,

106
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
the thing itself is equal to zero.

107
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:18,000
So, trying to put two particles into the same state always gives you zero.

108
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Anti-commutators take...

109
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:25,000
Anti-commutators give you fermions, which cannot go in the same state.

110
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:29,000
There's an interesting peculiarity here.

111
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,000
For bosons...

112
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:36,000
For bosons, there's a clear mathematical distinction

113
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:40,000
between creation operators and annihilation operators.

114
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Um...

115
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,000
Even if you didn't know what...

116
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:48,000
what the devil these things stood for,

117
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
when you write out the commutation,

118
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
we don't... we have no idea what these things stand for.

119
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:56,000
We just know that there's this algebraic structure

120
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,000
that some kind of creation...

121
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:01,000
some sort of object...

122
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:04,000
Let's not put daggers on for now.

123
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,000
It doesn't matter. Daggers or no daggers.

124
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:08,000
Some sort of objects...

125
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:15,000
Commute.

126
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,000
These things commute.

127
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,000
No. I'm sorry.

128
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,000
I wanted to take...

129
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Side dagger equals one.

130
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,000
Here we are.

131
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,000
This way.

132
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Equals one.

133
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,000
That's a harmonic oscillator.

134
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:35,000
Or it could just be a creation and annihilation operator for a boson.

135
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,000
Okay?

136
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:42,000
Could you mistake which one is the boson operator...

137
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,000
which one is the creation operator

138
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,000
and which one is the annihilation operator?

139
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Well, if you try to switch them,

140
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:55,000
if you try to replace A by A dagger,

141
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:58,000
and A dagger by A,

142
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:01,000
this is very definitely not equal to one.

143
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,000
In fact, what is it equal to?

144
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Minus one, right?

145
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,000
Combinator.

146
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Commutator.

147
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
If you switch the two things,

148
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,000
the commutator changes.

149
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,000
This is minus one.

150
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,000
And you could always tell,

151
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:17,000
even if I didn't label these as A and A dagger,

152
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,000
if I just labeled them as A and B

153
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,000
and asked you which one is the creation operator

154
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,000
and which one is the annihilation operator,

155
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,000
what you do is you look at the commutators,

156
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:29,000
and if the commutator is plus one,

157
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,000
then the first one here is the creation operator

158
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,000
and the second one is the annihilation operator.

159
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
There's no way to make a mistake.

160
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,000
So...

161
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:40,000
And in fact,

162
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,000
creation operators and annihilation operators

163
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,000
are fundamentally different.

164
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:48,000
Here's the stack of all possible states.

165
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,000
N equals zero.

166
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,000
N equals one.

167
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,000
N equals two.

168
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,000
Creation operators, just mathematically,

169
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:59,000
creation operators do not annihilate any state.

170
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,000
They just take you up the ladder.

171
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,000
And since the ladder never ends,

172
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,000
a creation operator

173
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,000
never runs out.

174
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,000
And that runs into the problem

175
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,000
that an annihilation operator does

176
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,000
if it annihilates too many times.

177
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,000
Annihilation operators,

178
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,000
when they get down to the bottom,

179
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:19,000
they give zero.

180
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Another way to say it

181
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,000
is that this spectrum of N

182
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:27,000
going from zero to infinity

183
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:31,000
is not the same if you turn it upside down.

184
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,000
You can go up to infinity,

185
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:36,000
but you can't go down past zero.

186
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,000
Okay, what about fermions?

187
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:41,000
Well, now you look at the fermion operators.

188
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:45,000
They also have creation and annihilation operators.

189
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:48,000
The difference, though,

190
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:52,000
is that you have anti-commutation relations

191
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:55,000
for fermions.

192
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,000
You also have creation operators.

193
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:02,000
You can create a fermion

194
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,000
plus one.

195
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,000
Anti-commutators are the same

196
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
if you interchange.

197
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,000
Why?

198
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,000
Because this is a a dagger

199
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,000
plus a dagger a.

200
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,000
It doesn't matter

201
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,000
which order they're in.

202
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,000
So just from the mathematical structure,

203
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:23,000
from the algebra,

204
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:26,000
there's no difference between creation operators.

205
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,000
It's true, they do different things,

206
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,000
but just looking at the algebra of them,

207
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,000
you can't tell the creation operators

208
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,000
from the annihilation operators.

209
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,000
And another way of seeing it,

210
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:39,000
is just to look at the possible

211
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:42,000
possible

212
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,000
occupation numbers

213
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,000
of a fermion.

214
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,000
Let's say it's a fermion with only one state.

215
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Fermion is in the ground state

216
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,000
of the hydrogen atom.

217
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,000
Okay, what can you have?

218
00:12:55,000 --> 00:13:00,000
The answer is you either have no particle

219
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,000
or you have one particle.

220
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,000
You can't have any more than one,

221
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,000
and you can't have any fewer than one.

222
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:08,000
And you can't have any fewer than zero.

223
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,000
What does the creation operator do?

224
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,000
It takes you from zero to one.

225
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:17,000
But what does it do when it hits one?

226
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
Nuh-uh, no state there.

227
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Annihilates the state, right, zero.

228
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,000
On the other hand,

229
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:26,000
the annihilation operator takes you down.

230
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:28,000
If there's a particle there, sure enough,

231
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,000
it can take you down,

232
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,000
but if there's no particle there,

233
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
end of story, you annihilate the state.

234
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,000
So there's a complete difference.

235
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,000
So there's a complete symmetry

236
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,000
between being empty and being filled

237
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,000
and replace creation operators

238
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,000
by annihilation operators.

239
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,000
Now, that doesn't mean they're physically the same.

240
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:49,000
It just means the algebra and the mathematics,

241
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:53,000
the symbols, you can't tell one from the other.

242
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Yes, question?

243
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,000
I had a question back when you were saying

244
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,000
if you try to have two fermions in the same place,

245
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:02,000
you'd have side dagger, side dagger, x equals zero.

246
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Why is that?

247
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:07,000
Why is that a contradiction or why is that not?

248
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,000
It's not a contradiction.

249
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,000
It just gives zero.

250
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,000
It doesn't give a state.

251
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:14,000
A state, a zero state is nothing.

252
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,000
So, but that, I'm just curious,

253
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:20,000
that's, so that's, that operator's squared, essentially, right?

254
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,000
Side dagger is squared, yeah.

255
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,000
Yeah.

256
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,000
If side, if you have an operator squared,

257
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:29,000
does that mean the operator is zero?

258
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:32,000
No, it means the operator's squared is zero.

259
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,000
No, no.

260
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:36,000
Look, here's a creation operator.

261
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,000
The creation operator squared,

262
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,000
there's nothing up here for it to give.

263
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,000
So it gives zero.

264
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:45,000
If you take the creation, for fermion,

265
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,000
for fermion, if you take the creation operator squared,

266
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,000
it's zero, there's nobody here.

267
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:53,000
If you take the annihilation operator squared, it's zero.

268
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:57,000
On the other hand, for bosons,

269
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:01,000
there is not this symmetry of filled and empty.

270
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,000
It's filled.

271
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:06,000
It's the symmetry of filled and empty,

272
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:10,000
two possible states and only two possible states

273
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:15,000
and no, um, for a single state of a fermion.

274
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
All right, that's going to play a role.

275
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,000
We'll get back to it.

276
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:21,000
What it says is that in some sense,

277
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,000
just pure mathematical sense,

278
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:27,000
you can interchange creation and annihilation operators.

279
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,000
Now, you may not want to do that

280
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,000
because they have physical significance,

281
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,000
but just as a, as a symbol,

282
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,000
but just as the algebraic structure of them,

283
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,000
you can interchange them.

284
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Okay, let's come back now to the Dirac equation,

285
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:44,000
the wonderful Dirac equation,

286
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:47,000
and let's pursue it.

287
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:52,000
Various things we want to understand.

288
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:59,000
We already figured out how to deal with the fact

289
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:03,000
that the simplest Dirac equation that we wrote down

290
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:06,000
doesn't have the possibility of having a mass.

291
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Let's just go back through it.

292
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:11,000
The simplest thing was just to write an equation

293
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:16,000
which was d by dt of psi,

294
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:18,000
let's put an i there,

295
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:25,000
i psi equals minus i d by dx psi.

296
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:27,000
This was for the case of one dimension.

297
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:29,000
Now, this psi here is some,

298
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,000
this is the wave,

299
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:35,000
is a, is let's say a wave function for a single particle.

300
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:38,000
For the moment, we're just doing single particles,

301
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,000
one particle.

302
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,000
This would be the Schrodinger equation for,

303
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,000
this would be the Hamiltonian over here.

304
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:49,000
This would be the Hamiltonian acting on psi

305
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,000
is equal to the momentum acting on psi.

306
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:56,000
And we will recognize this as just a theory

307
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,000
in which the energy of a particle

308
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
is equal to its momentum.

309
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Okay.

310
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:06,000
Energy equal momentum is a relativistic massless particle.

311
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:09,000
For mass, you want p squared,

312
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:14,000
sorry, e squared equals p squared plus m squared.

313
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,000
All right, so this was a failure

314
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,000
as a theory of one-dimensional electrons

315
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,000
because one-dimensional electrons moving on a wire

316
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,000
or something have a mass.

317
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:26,000
Okay, we figured out what to do with that.

318
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:29,000
We introduce a second species of electrons,

319
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:32,000
which this, these were right-moving electrons.

320
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:35,000
These were waves which moved strictly to the right.

321
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:39,000
The time derivative is minus their space derivative.

322
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,000
That means they move to the right.

323
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,000
So wave packets just propagate off

324
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:48,000
with constant velocity, speed of light.

325
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,000
Okay.

326
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:53,000
What you want to do is you want to invent another species

327
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,000
which propagates to the left.

328
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:58,000
So we could call this one psi one.

329
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:02,000
And we invent another one,

330
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:06,000
h psi two, a completely different particle,

331
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:10,000
equals minus p psi two,

332
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:13,000
a particle whose energy is minus the momentum.

333
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:17,000
And this just interchanges plus momentum in that direction,

334
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:20,000
right, with minus momentum in that direction.

335
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:24,000
And so this particle clearly propagates to the left.

336
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:27,000
Then we combined these two equations

337
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,000
by taking psi one and psi two

338
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:32,000
and making a column vector out of them.

339
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Quantum mechanically, this means the particle

340
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:42,000
can either be of one type or the second type.

341
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:45,000
So there's a new degree of freedom we discovered.

342
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,000
The new degree, or we were inventing,

343
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,000
a new degree of freedom,

344
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:51,000
which is above and beyond the momentum of the particle.

345
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,000
It's, it's handedness.

346
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,000
Does it move to the right or does it move to the left?

347
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Incidentally, this particle can have negative energy

348
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,000
or positive energy,

349
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,000
because p can be positive or negative.

350
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,000
But in either case, it goes to the right.

351
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,000
This one can have positive energy or negative energy.

352
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:11,000
In either case, it goes to the left.

353
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,000
Okay.

354
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:19,000
Then we, then, uh, we invented a matrix.

355
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,000
The matrix was alpha.

356
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:26,000
Alpha, oops, that's gamma.

357
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,000
Lie down, alpha.

358
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,000
Get on your side and be alpha.

359
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:43,000
And this says that psi one

360
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:47,000
is an eigenvector of alpha with eigenvalue plus one,

361
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:50,000
and psi two is an eigenvector of alpha with minus one.

362
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:53,000
And now we can combine these two equations.

363
00:19:53,000 --> 00:20:01,000
And just write that h psi,

364
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:04,000
this is supposed to be a, a simple psi,

365
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:10,000
h psi is equal to alpha times p psi.

366
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,000
What does this mean?

367
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:16,000
This means that if alpha is plus one, h is p.

368
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:19,000
If alpha is minus one, h is minus p.

369
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:22,000
So we have both of them in the same structure here.

370
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:28,000
At the cost of doubling the number of components of the field.

371
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Okay.

372
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
That didn't get us any, that didn't get us a mass,

373
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,000
but at least got us things going in both directions.

374
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,000
Then we did one more trick.

375
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:44,000
We invented a, another matrix that's called beta.

376
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,000
And that one looks like this, one, one.

377
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
Now the fact that these happen to be Pauli matrices

378
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,000
is somewhat incidental at this point.

379
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,000
They're just matrices for the moment.

380
00:20:54,000 --> 00:21:00,000
And instead of writing h is equal to alpha p,

381
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:04,000
h is equal to alpha p, that's that equation down there,

382
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:11,000
plus p or minus p, depending on the sign of alpha,

383
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:15,000
we added another term, beta times m.

384
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:20,000
Okay, now here's some things about alpha and beta.

385
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:26,000
Alpha squared and beta squared are one.

386
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:31,000
And alpha beta plus beta alpha equals zero.

387
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,000
You can check that.

388
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:36,000
Just check that if you multiply them in one order,

389
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,000
you get one thing.

390
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:39,000
If you multiply them in the other order,

391
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,000
you get the other thing, and they cancel.

392
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:44,000
You might say that alpha and beta anticommute, and it's true,

393
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:48,000
but don't confuse that with the anticommutation of the fields.

394
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,000
Okay.

395
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:54,000
So alpha and beta anticommute, they each square to one.

396
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:57,000
Now consider h squared.

397
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,000
That's the square of the energy.

398
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:02,000
That's the operator that governs the square of the energy.

399
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:06,000
Well, that's going to have one term, which is alpha squared p squared,

400
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:10,000
another term, which is beta squared m squared,

401
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:17,000
and then yet another term, which is alpha beta plus beta alpha p times m.

402
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,000
But we were lucky.

403
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:23,000
Alpha beta times beta alpha is identically equal to zero,

404
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:33,000
and so the only terms that are there are p squared plus m squared,

405
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:40,000
which is exactly what we want for a relativistic particle with mass.

406
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,000
Okay.

407
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:45,000
So we manage by combining a left-moving and a right-moving

408
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:48,000
and then coupling the left-moving and the right-moving

409
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:50,000
through this matrix beta.

410
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,000
The matrix beta does couple them together.

411
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:56,000
We end up with a particle with a mass.

412
00:22:56,000 --> 00:23:03,000
It's in this sense that a mass term is a mass term in the Hamiltonian

413
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:07,000
is something which sort of switches you from left-moving to right-moving.

414
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,000
Well, it doesn't really do that.

415
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,000
It just gives the particle a mass,

416
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:14,000
but you can picture it as causing transitions between left and right,

417
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,000
moving to the left and moving to the right.

418
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:19,000
And if you can have transitions between left and right,

419
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,000
you might start to think, well,

420
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:24,000
maybe it even makes sense to think of a particle at rest.

421
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,000
Pss, pss, pss, pss, pss, pss, pss.

422
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:28,000
Sort of at rest.

423
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,000
At rest, good.

424
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,000
You can have a massive particle at rest.

425
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,000
You can't have a massless particle.

426
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,000
What are you doing?

427
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,000
I'm filming you.

428
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,000
Oh, okay.

429
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,000
I have a question.

430
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:42,000
Is there more to the physical interpretation of having both types of particles?

431
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:44,000
It is what it is.

432
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:45,000
I...

433
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,000
Is there more to it?

434
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,000
We'll get there.

435
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:50,000
Yeah, there is more to it,

436
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,000
but at this point, that's what the...

437
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:54,000
That's all there is, yeah.

438
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Sometimes things are just abstract.

439
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:00,000
Sometimes that's all there is to it.

440
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,000
All right, so then comes the question,

441
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,000
how do we do this in three dimensions?

442
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,000
Three dimensions instead of one dimension.

443
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:11,000
Three dimensions of space.

444
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:14,000
Okay, so let's go back.

445
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:30,000
Let's start with what will turn out to be the case which is massless.

446
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:33,000
Will turn out to be a case which can't have a mass.

447
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,000
Here's what we're going to do.

448
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:39,000
We have three dimensions of space.

449
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:42,000
It wouldn't make sense to have only one alpha.

450
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,000
We can have px.

451
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,000
We can have py.

452
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,000
And we can have pz.

453
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,000
This looks like it wants to be some sort of product

454
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:51,000
of a degree of freedom with p,

455
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,000
but p is a vector.

456
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,000
What do we get to make...

457
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:58,000
What do we get to multiply by vectors

458
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:00,000
to make things which are invariant?

459
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,000
Other vectors.

460
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,000
We take dot products of vectors.

461
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:07,000
So here's what Dirac thought to himself.

462
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:10,000
He thought this alpha here must be a vector

463
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:12,000
if we're going to multiply it by p

464
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:14,000
and make something which is rotationally invariant.

465
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:17,000
That means it must have three components.

466
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:19,000
It must have three components.

467
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:28,000
So he said, let's try the equation h equals alpha dot p.

468
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:42,000
This means alpha sub x px plus alpha sub y py plus alpha sub z pz.

469
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,000
Okay.

470
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:48,000
What do the alphas have to do to make this sensible?

471
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:50,000
For the moment, we're not going to try to make a mass.

472
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,000
We're going to make a massless equation.

473
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:56,000
So what is the right formula for our massless particle?

474
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,000
It's energy versus momentum.

475
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:02,000
The answer is energy squared equals momentum squared,

476
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:06,000
but that means energy squared equals px squared plus py squared plus pz squared.

477
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,000
That's what we want to get.

478
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:13,000
h squared equals px squared plus py squared plus py squared.

479
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:16,000
What happens if we square this thing over here?

480
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:20,000
Well, we'll get terms which are alpha x squared times px squared.

481
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,000
That's okay.

482
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:25,000
That just means we want alpha x squared to equal 1.

483
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:29,000
Likewise with alpha y.

484
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:33,000
Alpha z squared equals 1.

485
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:36,000
But now we want to make sure the cross terms aren't there.

486
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:39,000
So we're going to have to make a massless equation.

487
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:41,000
So we're going to have to make a massless equation.

488
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:44,000
But now we want to make sure the cross terms aren't there.

489
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:48,000
When we multiply out the cross terms, we get px times py,

490
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:53,000
and it will multiply alpha x alpha y plus alpha y alpha x.

491
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:55,000
That's what will happen.

492
00:26:55,000 --> 00:27:03,000
So we had better have that alpha x alpha y plus alpha y alpha x equals 0.

493
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:08,000
And likewise for the other combinations.

494
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:11,000
Same with x and z, same with y and z.

495
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:20,000
So Dirac says, can I find three matrices which each one squared is 1

496
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:24,000
and which mutually anticommute?

497
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:26,000
And the answer to that is easy.

498
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:28,000
Pauli matrices.

499
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:31,000
The three Pauli matrices do exactly that.

500
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:36,000
So if we say alpha x is equal to sigma x,

501
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:40,000
the Pauli matrix equals 1 1 0 0.

502
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:50,000
Alpha y equals sigma y equals what?

503
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:56,000
Minus 1, sorry, minus i i 0 0.

504
00:27:56,000 --> 00:28:02,000
And finally, the last one is alpha z equals sigma z.

505
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:07,000
And that's the easy one to remember, 1 minus 1.

506
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:09,000
And we got it.

507
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:17,000
In other words, our Hamiltonian h is equal to sigma dot p.

508
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:24,000
You can think of this as a particle whose,

509
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:28,000
well, it's a particle that has a spin, that's the sigma,

510
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:31,000
and a particle that has a momentum,

511
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:33,000
and the energy is proportional to the dot product

512
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:37,000
or the component of spin along the direction of motion.

513
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:39,000
Okay?

514
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:41,000
Good.

515
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:43,000
So it's a massless particle,

516
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:49,000
but it has the odd behavior that its spin is always,

517
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:54,000
well, let's go back.

518
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,000
Okay.

519
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,000
Sigma dot p.

520
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:02,000
Its energy is proportional to the component of its spin

521
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:05,000
along the momentum direction.

522
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:09,000
Now, the component of a spin is always plus or minus 1.

523
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:12,000
So it sounds like there are two cases here.

524
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:16,000
One case where the spin is literally along the momentum,

525
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:18,000
pointing along the momentum,

